[[滋賀県]]と[[京都府]]の境に所在する山で、標高593.4m。
[[東海道新幹線]]と[[東海道本線]]のトンネルが通じており、麓には[[京阪京津線]]が通っている。[[東海自然歩道]]がこの山を通っている。
{{Japan-geo-stub}}

'''Otowa Mountain''' is a mountain located on the border between Kyoto Prefecture and Shiga Prefecture. It is the highest peak in Yamashina Ward of Kyoto City, with an elevation of 593.2 meters. A triangulation point is located near the summit, with part of the summit area belonging to Kyoto Prefecture. == Overview == Situated to the east of the Yamashina Basin and southwest of Lake Biwa, Otowa Mountain once formed part of the border between Yamashiro Province and Ōmi Province. The valley between it and Aisaka Mountain has long served as a key transportation route. Many classical poets—including {{ill|Kakinomoto no Hitomaro|ja|柿本人麻呂|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ariwara no Narihira|ja|在原業平|12=draft}}—have celebrated Otowa Mountain as a poetic motif. == Transportation == A tunnel of the Tōkaidō Shinkansen (known as the Otowa Mountain Tunnel) passes directly beneath the summit, while the Keihan Keishin Line runs through the mountain valley between Otowa Mountain and Aisaka Mountain. Additionally, the Tōkai Nature Trail traverses the area, linking routes from the Ishiyama-dera side to the vicinity of Aisaka Mountain. == References == {{Reflist}} == See Also == * [[List of mountain names in Japan]] * Biwa Lake Broadcasting – headquartered on the Shiga side.
